thread.title_full: No. 1 Bergen Catholic cruises past St. Augustine for 6th straight state championship

author: Patrick Lanni | NJ Advance Media for NJ.com
title: No. 1 Bergen Catholic cruises past St. Augustine for 6th straight state championship
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Bergen Catholic needed every minute and every second to get by Delbarton on Friday in the North Jersey, Non-Public A final. 
On Sunday, Bergen Catholic needed just 57 minutes to handle St. Augustine and officially clinch its sixth straight state championship with a 54-15 win over St. Augustine in the Non-Public A final at Pine Belt Arena. 
With the win, Bergen Catholic put the finishing touches on its fourth straight year as the state’s top-ranked team. 
Bergen Catholic won 11 bouts, won by fall in five of them and junior Sage Mosco officially ended the Crusaders’ championship season with a 3-0 decision over Sean Lenzsch at 195.
